<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910416-0123</DOCNO><DOCID>910416-0123.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Affiliated Publications Inc.:   Media Concern Posts Loss   Of $993,000 for 1st Quarter</HL><DATE>04/16/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   AFP</CO><MS>CONSUMER CYCLICAL (CYC)</MS><IN>EARNINGS (ERN)MEDIA, PUBLISHING, BROADCASTING, ELECTRONIC PUBLISHING (MED)</IN><NS>EARNINGS (ERN)</NS><RE>MASSACHUSETTS (MA)</RE><LP>   Affiliated Publications Inc., which owns the Boston Globe,reported a first-quarter loss because of advertising declinesand the cost of covering the Mideast war.   The Boston media concern said it had a loss of $993,000,or one cent a share. In the year-ago quarter, it earned $6.5million, or nine cents a share.</LP><TEXT>   Revenue declined 3.8% to $128.6 million from $133.7million. Affiliated said advertising revenue fell to $88million from $97.8 million. Revenue at the Boston Globenewspaper unit fell 10% to $92.8 million.   William O. Taylor, chairman, said that costs related towar coverage increased expenses about $1 million.   In New York Stock Exchange composite trading yesterday,Affiliated Publications' shares closed at $9.125, down 37.5cents.</TEXT></DOC>